---
description: Enforce descriptive variable names in props, maps, and destructuring
globs: "**/*.{ts,tsx}"
alwaysApply: false
---

# No Single-Letter Variable Names

Never use single-letter identifiers for props, map/filter/reduce callbacks, or destructured bindings.

```tsx
// ❌ BAD
<BinaryStatusCard b={b} />;
items.map((b) => <Card key={b.id} b={b} />);
const { b } = props;

// ✅ GOOD
<BinaryStatusCard binary={binary} />;
items.map((binary) => <Card key={binary.id} binary={binary} />);
const { binary } = props;
```

Choose names that reflect what the value represents: `job`, `item`, `binary`, `category`, `file`, etc.
